{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> σκολιός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> <b>curved, bent</b> (opposed to ὀρθός, εὐθύς), σ. σίδηρος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.86; σ. σκίπωνι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 65 (_anapaest meter_) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of rivers and paths, <b>winding</b>, ποταμός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.185, compare 2.29; Μαίανδρος σ. εἰς ὑπερβολήν 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 12.8.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἶμος, ἀτραπός, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 4.1541, 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 478, etc.; ῥηγμῖνες 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 367b14; λαβύρινθος 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 311; πλέγμα ἕλικος “Anthologia Graeca” 7.24 (4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus); πλοκαμῖδες 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 14.182 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>twisted, tangled</b>, βάτος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.315 (4th-3rd c.BC: Zenodotus Grammaticus or 3rd c.BC: Rhianus Epicus), compare 11.33 (1st c.AD: Philippus Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς τὸ σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 37. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>bent sideways</b>, δουλείη κεφαλή, σκολιή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 536; γένυες 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 203 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἵππος σ. <b>crooked made</b> or <b>going askew</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 253d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>crooked</b>, i.e. <b>unjust, unrighteous</b>, θέμιστες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.387 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μῦθοι, δίκαι, [<a href=\"java